CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 22, 1969, pg. 10, reads: "Admiring Gifts - Little Robin Bullard is pictured admiring some of the lovely gifts which she received on her 11th birthday. The party was given by Mrs. Margaret Bullard of Bedford Avenue who said it was for her 'favorite granddaughter.'  A number of Robin's friends were on hand to help her celebrate and all had loads of fun. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Robin Bullard posed behind coffee table with eleventh birthday cake, surrounded by other girls, including two on right wearing identical two toned plaid dresses, and boys, posed in home of Margaret Bullard, 2801 Bedford Avenue
